title: Infant mortality rate in Greece 2018
summary: This is a line chart with an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Deaths per 1,000 live births, containing a total of 11 data points.
Overall Deaths per 1,000 live births has increased over the Year.
Deaths per 1,000 live births is roughly constant from 2008 to 2011, gradually increasing from 2011 to 2015, roughly constant from 2015 to 2016, and finally slightly decreasing from 2016 to 2018.
The most drastic increase took place within the Year 2014 and 2015.
The highest Deaths per 1,000 live births, of value 3.8 was reached at Year 2015, and 2016
The lowest Deaths per 1,000 live births, of value 3.3 was reported at Year 2008,  2009,  2010, and 2011
